\begin_layout Chapter
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Description of the given problem
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will project and implement PowerEnjoy, which is a car-sharing service
 that offers only electric cars.
 The price varies just depending on the real use of each individual rental
 of the car.
 The system allows clients to reserve a car via mobile or web app, using
 GPS or an address to identify client’s zone and find a car in the same
 zone.
 On the other side the mobile app allows operators to know what they must
 do.
 The system provide the functionality normally provided by car-sharing services.
 Indeed the system let the registered users to see cars location through
 the city and to reserve a car until one hour before.
 Moreover, PowerEnjoy wants to incentivize the virtuous behaviors of the
 users through discounts for those users that park in power grid station,
 charge the car and travel with more than two passengers, and penalties
 for those who leave the car with more than 80% of battery empty or far
 away from a power grid station.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The system offers also a money saving option that users can enable inside
 the car, which provides information about the station where to leave the
 car to get a discount.
 This station is determined to ensure a uniform distribution of cars in
 the city and depends both on destination of the user and on the availability
 of power plugs at the selected station.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Goals
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Visitor
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G1] Allow visitors to register in the system
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Client
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G2] Allows users to login in the system 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G3] Users must be able to find the locations of available cars 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G4] Allows users to request for the reservation of a car until one hour
 before 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G5] Allows users to unlock the reserved car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G6] Allows users to know the current battery level of each available cars
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G7] Allows users to know which are the “safe area” 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G8] Users should enable the money saving option in the car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G9] Users should know where the power grid stations are 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G10] Users can report if the reserved car has damage 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G11] Allows users to cancel a reservation 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G12] Allows users to have discount 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G13] Allows users to end the ride 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Operator
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G14] Allows operators to login in the system 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G15] Allows operators to know all the information of cars 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G16] Allows operators to unlock cars 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G17] Operators should receive a notification for incoming request of reparation
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G18] Operators must be able to report the operation they have done 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G19] Operators should receive a notification for moving a car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G20] Operators should receive a notification for charging a car 
\end_layout

